{"schema_version":"1","crate":"keystoreada","version":"1.4.2","id":"5a9f9d0f55c4b20c","name":"Util.Encoders.AES","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":62,"column":9},"code":"package Util.Encoders.AES","documentation":{"description":"== AES Encryption and decryption ==\nThe `Util.Encoders.AES` package implements the basis for AES encryption\nand decryption used by the `Util.Streams.AES` package for AES streams.\nSeveral encryption modes are available and described by the `AES_Mode`\ntype and the padding is controlled by the `AES_Padding` type.\nThe encryption is provided by methods on the `Encoder` type.  The `Set_Key`\nprocedure configures the encryption key and AES encryption mode.  The key\nmust be 16, 24 or 32 bytes as specified by the pre-condition.  Then, the\n`Transform` procedure is called as needed to encrypt the content in a\ndestination buffer.  It returns the position of the last encoded byte as\nwell as the position of the last encrypted byte.  It can be called several\ntimes if the data to encrypt does not fit in the destination buffer.\nAt the end, it is important to call the `Finish` procedure so that it\nhandles correctly the last AES block which may contain the last encrypted\nbytes as well as optional padding.  An encryption function is shown below:\n\n  function Encrypt (Key   : in Secret_Key;\n                    Src   : in Stream_Element_Array) return Stream_Element_Array is\n     Size    : constant Stream_Element_Offset := AES.Align (Src'Length);\n     Cipher  : Util.Encoders.AES.Encoder;\n     Encoded, Last : Stream_Element_Offset;\n     Result  : Stream_Element_Array (1 .. Size);\n  begin\n     Cipher.Set_Key (Key, AES.ECB);\n     Cipher.Transform (Src, Result (Result'First .. Result'Last - 16),\n                       Last, Encoded);\n     Cipher.Finish (Result (Last + 1 .. Result'Last), Last);\n     return Result;\n  end Encrypt;\n\nWith AES, the encryption result is always a multiple of AES block size (16 bytes).\nThe `Align` function allows to easily compute the expected encrypted size.\n\nDecrypting a content follows the same principles but with the `Decoder` type.\nThe source array must be a multiple of AES block and the last AES block may\ncontain some padding.  The `Finish` procedure will then indicate the last\nvalid byte in the decrypted buffer.\n\n  function Decrypt (Key   : in Secret_Key;\n                    Src   : in Stream_Element_Array) return Stream_Element_Array is\n     Size     : constant Stream_Element_Offset := Src'Length;\n     Decipher : Util.Encoders.AES.Decoder;\n     Result   : Stream_Element_Array (1 .. Size);\n     Encoded, Last : Stream_Element_Offset;\n  begin\n     Decipher.Set_Key (Key, AES.ECB);\n     Decipher.Set_Padding (AES.PKCS7_PADDING);\n     Decipher.Transform (Src, Result, Last, Encoded);\n     Decipher.Finish (Result (Last + 1 .. Result'Last), Last);\n     return Result (Result'First .. Last);\n  end Decrypt;"},"simple_types":[{"id":"9dff8206d83074e9","name":"AES_Mode","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.AES_Mode","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":64,"column":9},"code":"type AES_Mode is (ECB, CBC, PCBC, CFB, OFB, CTR);"},{"id":"d84a82665b86b7cb","name":"AES_Padding","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.AES_Padding","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":66,"column":9},"code":"type AES_Padding is (NO_PADDING, ZERO_PADDING, PKCS7_PADDING);"},{"id":"9fa4d8f39d8e33c9","name":"Key_Type","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Key_Type","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":68,"column":9},"code":"type Key_Type is private;"}],"array_types":[{"id":"70a3accb1bfeedbf","name":"Word_Block_Type","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Word_Block_Type","kind":"ada_array_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":87,"column":9},"code":"type Word_Block_Type is array (1 .. 4) of Interfaces.Unsigned_32;"}],"tagged_types":[{"id":"19bcfc710fe85967","name":"Cipher","qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Cipher","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/sys/encoders/util-encoders-aes.ads","line":120,"column":9},"code":"type Cipher is tagged limited private;","derived_types":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Decoder","id":"5b24ba5639a28bc9","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Encoder","id":"48d81ec616c6482a","unit":"util-encoders-aes"}],"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Has_Key","id":"8e5aeca1ec3e5331","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Padding","id":"f36da39a5d6752cf","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Set_IV","id":"2f32fba4ddc759dd","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Set_IV","id":"cdcad9e8f295ede7","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Set_IV","id":"5d7934be2af4fa4a","unit":"util-encoders-aes"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Encoders.AES.Set_Padding","id":"519810a7b1271c81","unit":"util-encoders-aes"}],"dispa